{
  "text": "As fluorescence depends both on the nature of the Kasha state and on the competition between several de-excitation processes, fluorescence lifetime is very sensitive to the environment. It allows for measurement of the oxygen concentration [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , viscosity [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , and pH [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
